{"text": "The lowest hypothetical or imaginary temperature at which gases are supposed to occupy zero volume is called Absolute zero.", "fibs": ["temperature"]}
{"text": "All gases obey Charles’ law at very low pressures and high temperatures.", "fibs": ["’"]}
